# patches/0008-room-ordering-presort.patch
#
# == SUPERSEDED ==
#
# This patch added a std::sort hack to RoomlistModel::initializeRooms()
# to pre-sort roomIdList by approximate_last_modification_ts.
#
# REASON FOR SUPERSEDING:
# The std::sort hack was useless because FilteredRoomlistModel (the proxy
# model) overrides the underlying list order anyway via its own lessThan()
# implementation. Worse, the sort happened only once at init time, so any
# subsequent sync would not maintain the order.
#
# FIXED PROPERLY BY:
# patches/new-files/src/BeeperReinitController.cpp now calls
# cache->updateLastMessageTimestamp() after each /messages response during
# Phase 3b of BeeperReinitWorker::process(). This ensures the room's
# approximate_last_modification_ts is written to the LMDB rooms database
# with the correct timestamp from the most recent event in the chunk.
# The FilteredRoomlistModel then sorts chronologically via its lessThan()
# override, which reads Timestamp from the model (which in turn reads from
# the cache's room info).
#
# After Phase 3b finishes, the worker invokes
# TimelineViewManager::initializeRoomlist() on the main thread via
# BlockingQueuedConnection, causing a full beginResetModel/endResetModel
# cycle so the UI re-reads all corrected timestamps.
